quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  28,1,"Tâ Sîn Mīm."
  28,2,"Those are the signs1of the Evident Scripture."
  28,3,"We read to yousg from the tiding of Moses and Pharaoh in truth for people who believe."
  28,4,"Indeed, Pharaoh became exalted in the land and divided its people into sects, deeming a faction of them weak and oppressed: slaughtering their sons while keeping their women alive(in bondage) . Indeed, he was one of the corrupters."
  28,5,"Thus We are willing to favor those who were deemed weak and oppressed in the land and to make them leaders and to make them the inheritors"